It is my understanding that &quot;under god&quot; was added later anyway.. in my opinion it should have never been added.<br>
<br>
It only makes sense..<br>
<br>
Originally... &quot;I pledge of allegiance to my flag and the Republic for which it stands - One nation indivisible - with liberty and justice for all.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;under god&quot; was added in 1954.. 12 years after the U.S congress recognized the pledge officially in 1942.<br>
<br>
Of course there were other changes.. &quot;to my flag&quot; was changed to &quot;to the Flag of the United States of America&quot;.<br>
